<p>Is there a way to add new data in an already set flash scope without erasing the previous data set ?</p>  <pre><code>Redirect(routes.Application.home).flashing("success" -&gt; "OK").flashing("but" -&gt; "BUT") </code></pre>  <p>results the same as :</p>  <pre><code>Redirect(routes.Application.home).flashing("but" -&gt; "BUT") </code></pre>  <p>I could do <code>flashing("success"-&gt;"OK", "but"-&gt;"BUT")</code> but I add the last flashed data in another object. Flashing data in a single call would require to rewrite a lot of things...</p>